cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on the comparison of deep learning algorithms with other machine learning algorithms on an unbalanced data set used for credit scoring. This topic is closely related to machine learning, particularly in the areas of classification and prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with credit scoring, which is a subfield of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR). The use of deep learning algorithms also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the optimization techniques used in neural networks, which is related to computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of various algorithms, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
